Package algorithms

Class FixedSizeSortedIntVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.FixedSizeSortedIntVector
  • public class FixedSizeSortedIntVector
extends java.lang.Object
    a class to hold a fixed number of items of type int which are kept in a sorted stated. 
     runtime complexity is:
     O(N * (lg_2(k) + smaller than k))
 where k is the fixed capacity and N is the number of times add is used
 (each insert is roughly log_2(k)).

 worse case runtime complexity is O(N * (k + lg_2(k)))
 best case runtime complexity is O(N * (1 + lg_2(k)))
    first implemented in project https://github.com/nking/curvature-scale-space-corners-and-transformations w/ Copyright (c) 2014 Climb With Your Feet and using The MIT License (MIT) then moved to this shared library project which has the same copyright and license.
    Author:
    nichole
